"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-sport-rowing-2024-0520-1450214-puspure-and-pazzaia-advance-to-olympic-qualifier-finals\", \"text\": \"Ireland's Sanita Puspure and Konan Pazzaia have advanced to their respective finals at the Olympic qualifier regatta in Switzerland.  The Lucerne event represents a last chance saloon for rowers bidding to make it to Paris this summer, and Puspure progressed to her single sculls final in particularly impressive fashion.  The 42-year-old clocked the fastest time of all tomorrow's finalists when she recorded a time of seven minutes 38 seconds to win her semi-final, with Switzerland's Aurelia-Maxima Katharina Janzen and Slovakia's Nina Kostanjsek her nearest pursuers.  Konan Pazzaia finished third in his single sculls semi-final behind Romania's Mihai Chiruta, with Tokyo silver medallist Kjetil Borch of Norway filling the runner-up berth.  The top two in Tuesday's finals will secure Olympic qualification.  \\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026. RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann, Ireland's National Public Service Media. RT\\u00c9 is not responsible for the content of external internet sites.  Images Courtesy of Getty Images.\"}"